1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:10,563
Now pay attention here,  each record in a partition receives a monotonically increasing integer called an offset, starting at 0.

2
00:00:10,513 --> 00:00:15,289
Offsets uniquely identify a record within a partition.

3
00:00:15,289 --> 00:00:20,789
Consumers track their position by storing the last processed offset.

